Finding Fuel: IOM Helps a Displaced Family Cook Safely



   Sana’a – The ongoing conflict in Yemen has driven the country to the
   brink of famine.

   [so20190826-blog.jpg?itok=KsGD85Ph]

A Mother’s Desperate Plea



   Somalia – It is estimated that there are around 323,000 Internally
   Displaced People currently in Baidoa, Bay region of Somalia. Drought
   has been one of the primary causes of displacement. With no water,
   there is a severe shortage of crops and livestock, leading to loss of
   livelihoods or even starvation.

   [20190531-turkey-blog1.jpg?itok=WHPUpaxz]

Community-Led Iftar Dinners Bring Solidarity, Unity, Inclusiveness to
Neighbourhoods in Turkey



   “Neighbours, friendship, and families. That’s what you see all around
   you,” said Mukhtar Seyit Ahmet Kanar of Fezi Paşa Neighborhood to IOM
   organizers at an iftar dinner in Nizip district just an hour outside of
   the southeastern province of Gaziantep.

