   Improving Health Access for Displaced Women and Girls in Iraq

   In 2014, when ISIL militants began their rampage, millions of Iraqis
   raced to flee their homes. From large cities and tiny villages, an
   estimated 1.6 million Internally Displaced Persons spread across Iraq.
